The Gym is so much more that physical health! 
.
Past year there have been so many ups and downs! So many big changes! Some of you know what’s going on and some of you think you know. At the end of the day this year has taught me so much about myself and others! But the biggest lessons I’ve learned are…. 
.
- Keep your head up because if you drop it you might miss opportunity that is standing right in front of you 
- Love hard but protect your heart (Mom)
- People that are meant to be in your life will never leave no matter what happens 
- Not everyone is your friend most people are not
- Don’t be afraid to open up to people you care about 
- Good Communication is one of the most important things in life! Learn To Communicate Face to Face not through text!
- Forgiveness of yourself and others is the hardest but best thing you can do for you mentally 
- Lastly smile and dance because why not 

So many big things happening, I hope you guy are here with me while I climb this mountain because those are the people I truly want at the top during the after party! 
.

There’s gonna be a time in life where you get punched so hard that your not sure if you can get up! 
.
Quitting will run through your head…. You’re gonna find yourself thinking: 
- why am I doing this 
- will this pay off 
- is this worth it 
The unknown is one of the scariest places ….. It’s easy to quit …. There will be times that your gonna break down, times that you will sit alone and cry, hyperventilating over these thoughts, you will ask yourself what did I do to deserve what I’m going through ….. but these little moments are so little in the grand scheme of things ….. it’s these moments that you will look back and thank yourself for not quitting …. As long as your keep moving …. Even if you get hit 10 steps back, as long as you keep moving forward your will be in a different place than you were yesterday! …. If you quit you will live in the EXACT PLACE you don’t want to be! Make the choice forget all the bull shit and start moving! 
.

Last Years Was A Roller Coaster! 
I lost a lot! My life was spiraling down hill! 
My friends @mlaurin18 and @dat.dude.derek asked me to come to @weareradiant ….. this was after years of my friends @ajamurai and @tony_watt  constantly inviting me to go as well! …… If you know me you know I’m a Lion, you know I’m a Wolf and show very little emotion because I deal with everyone else’s on the daily! I sat there my first day listening to @aaronrburke speak “it’s not you It’s Me” and it was like no one else was in the room but me and him! 
So I sat there eyes full of tears …. Thinking about why this was all happening to me and what I did to deserve some of these things! I thought, “I know exactly what I did and mistakes I made for some things” but why others! I was lost! But I was not gonna sit there and blame anyone but myself!
.
I’ll tell you the Saddest Part of my Healing and Recovery is knowing I had the most friends, When I was the worst version of myself! Im so Grateful for those friends that actually asked me what’s going on and know what’s happening in my life because they cared! This was truly Gods way of clearing all the people who I thought were family, out of my life! This was Gods way Of separating me from a Toxic place! This was Gods way of waking me up and pulling me back in! I’m so grateful to have people that support me no matter what and are interested in what’s going on because they actually care! 
Sunday was a huge day for me! 
I chose to give my life back to Christ! 
I got Baptized again! 
It was the best feeling in the world! I have to also thank my biggest supporter through this Journey, my girlfriend  @stephaniemanah she doesn’t know it but she kept me high on some Really Really Low days! I can’t thank her enough! 
If I tagged you in this ….. just know that you mean the world to me for being there when I needed a real friend and you played a very important and specific role on my Journey!
Thank You for make my birthday perfect! @stephaniemanah
